
    Tim Berners-Lee (pictured) wins the Turing Award for inventing the World Wide Web, the first web browser, and the protocols and algorithms that allow the Web to scale.
    
    
    In the Syrian Civil War, a chemical attack in Khan Shaykhun kills more than 70 people and injures hundreds.
    
    
    In college basketball, the South Carolina Gamecocks win the NCAA women's tournament and the North Carolina Tar Heels win the men's tournament.
    
    
    A bombing in the Saint Petersburg Metro kills at least 14 people and injures more than 45 others.
    
    
    The annual Boat Races are held, with Oxford winning the men's race and Cambridge winning the women's race.
